metadata.name: let me fall #300
metadata.description:
A study of form, empty spaces, panic attacks, asymmetry, tinnitus, chaos, and the never-ending journey to obtain imperfection. 

30 Matisse-inspired palettes.

2-6 – increase resolution.

“f” – add more noise to iteration at current resolution.
“n” – redraw at current resolution without noise.
“s” – save export.

Please be patient while drawing at higher resolutions, it can take quite a while.

Created with p5js.

metadata.name: Egos #28
metadata.description:
"Art comes to people from God. Now it is in the will of man to create. therefore, art is the representation of the feelings of the free individual. The old must be erased and the new reigned." 
 Charles Baudelaire

 In this collection, geometric forms created by symbolic individuals are examined.

* You have to be patient for the animations to work properly.
* Save image: press 's' to save the current image as png.

* Owners can get 6 free per person for their support in my previous three collections. 
 Among the new collectors, 5 works will be open to access.
 20 percent of the royalty will belong to the minters.

metadata.name: Aftershock #39
metadata.description:
Turkey was hit by two devastating earthquakes at 6/02/2023 effecting multiple cities.

Aftershock is created to help and support people in earthquake region. 100% of the revenue from primary sales will be send to non governmental organization AHBAP after it's converted to ethereum. All donation will sent from atimtay.eth and will be shared publicly from my twitter account


Artwork info:

Aftershock is based on "Metropolix IX' algorithm. In Metropolis the parameter space was constrained and the cells were painted in a fashion which would create city silhouettes. In Aftershock i removed the constraints and changed the all rulesets and palettes which would give us chaos maybe you can call it a collapsed city.


Features:

6 color palettes and 1 monochrome 
3 subdivison levels 2,3,4 
2 aspect ratios 
10 divison styles 
and some other hidden randomized parameters which doesn't appear on the features but effecting overall outcome

Press 1 to 8 to export PNG at increasing resolution

Murat Atimtay 2023 www.atimtay.xyz

metadata.name: contrapuntos #589
metadata.description:
Musical counterpoint is to me an abstraction of the layered, intertwining rhythms of every activity we carry on in our lives. With a global tempo typically set in days, we fit all sorts of temporal structures where our joys and fears live and play out over the span of our lives. This series is a metaphorical transposition of the musical counterpoint into a visual space, sometimes with repeating patterns, sometimes with broken structures, sometimes isolated notes / hours / souls.

Artwork by Marcelo Soria-Rodríguez, @msoriaro. Made with p5js & glsl.

metadata.name: Momentum #98
metadata.description:
In our new project, we explore the possibilities and tools of generative art. This time we were interested in the aesthetics of particles. When static turns into movement, and the predicted composition becomes spontaneous - the experiment continues.
This project was created with P5.js.
March 2023.
Press 'S' to save a PNG file.

metadata.name: Contraformas #80
metadata.description:
Shapes are drawn on a space-filling grid against other shapes, using a random walk algorithm. then they are separated with a random offset, hence the name counterforms (contraformas).

created by @mdollinger with p5js

metadata.name: Morixels MegaColab #3 #190
metadata.description:
🟥 One of the greatest collaborations between 33 Artists 🟥

In this collection, you will see a variety of artworks by artists in the following fields:

🔘 Physical painting
🔘 Digital painting
🔘 Illustration
🔘 3D art
🔘 Collage
🔘 Photography
🔘 Photomontage
🔘 Pixel art
🔘 Voxel art
🔘 AI art
🔘 and Music 

In this Collab, 31 artists, including myself as the MegaColab designer and also the Art Director, have produced 160 Artworks. I also designed the frames as Generative Art using pure JavaScript code.

For the first time in this Collab, we asked a musician friend to compose music specifically for this Collab, and you will hear four of his compositions.

Additionally, I myself created four pieces of music with the help of artificial intelligence.

If you didn't Hear the music, click on the image or click on the "Open" button below the image, and then click on the image to play the music.
